reviewText: I got this DVD today and I liked it. It contains the music video,the making of the video,and commericals for the Osbourne Family album(there's a few.)But it was a fun DVD.If you're a real Kelly fan,then you NEED it.
I bought the Kelly Osbourne DVD and it was worth my money... and it has the video, making the video and MTV promos on it!

This DVD rocks!  I was just expecting a music video and something promoting her album, but there was a lot more.  This DVD single has more than any other one I've seen.  The making of the video is so cool.  You get to see what it was really like behind the scenes and how a video is made.  The Osbourne Family TV spots were great too!  This is a definite must-have for all Kelly fans!  And if you're not a Kelly fan, buy the DVD and I'm sure you'll become one!  I would recommend this DVD to everyone.  Keep rockin' Kelly!

Record companies need to release more of these GREAT bargain priced DVD singles!  Kelly's DVD contains her "Papa Don't Preach" video (in 5.1 Surround Sound... it sounds great), the "Making Of" her video, and promo spots for "The Osbournes Family Album" cd (featuring Kelly, Jack, Sharon, and Ozzy).  There's about 30 minutes of stuff on this DVD, so it's well worth it.  It comes in a standard plastic snap DVD case.  Well, it's not that standard. It's YELLOW!  I'm surprised it's not pink to match Kelly's hair!
Kelly's DVD is a great precursor to "The Osbournes" DVD set (yes, all of the episodes are coming out on sparkling DVD!), due out later this year, and to Kelly's upcoming album.
This is probably one of the best DVD singles that I own (and I have several.)  It contains more stuff than any of the other ones I have and you can't beat the price!
